# 6.-UIElements
**What is a UIElement?**

A base class for most of the Windows Runtime UI objects that have visual appearance and can process basic input as part of your app's user interface

**What does UI stand for?**

User Interface

**What symbol signals that a connections has been broken in your View Controller Class?**

The filled circle will be blank and empty

**How can you reconnect a broken link on a UIElement from your View Controller Class to the storyboard?**

ctrl, click a button and drag below VDL, type...
 imageView.image = UIImage.init(named: "blablabla")

**What symbol signals that a connections has been broken in your Storyboard Connections Inspector?**

A yellow triangle

**How to remove a broken connections in the connections inspector?**

Delete the link with the caution sign next to it and re-do the function

**How to link a UIElement to View Controller class?**

Click 'Assets.xcassets' in the left bar. and drag your images into the blank column

**How to embed a navigation controller?**



**Where to keep local images within your project?**

In 'Assets.xcassets'

**Describe an IBAction?**

Completes an action you wish to carry out
You place these below ViewDidLoad

**Desicbe an IBOutlet?**

They don't complete actions, they are just there e.g. label, image
You place these above ViewDidLoad

**Label the following elements as outlets and/or actions (it might be useful to add snippets of code in here):**

Slider - Action
Button - Action
Label - Outlet
Progress Bar - 
Image View - Outlet
